        "ts": "1761837952.839069",
        "client_msg_id": "4f7c0629-c008-4d1e-8db7-dc89ea165d8a",
        "text": "in 2003, I was hired to develop the SDK used to develop audio effect plug-ins for this [line of hardware](<https:\/\/www.roland.com\/us\/products\/vs-2400cd\/>). The embedded toolchain was horrible, and I badly needed to have a profiler that didn't exist, so made my own by emitting MIDI messages that were recorded into a sequencer, then wrote a small Python app to convert that to usable output.",
